#N canvas 50 50 950 670 10;
#X text 20 15 wall.pd v2 - NES-style pitched noise burst with pitch sweep + low-pass shaping;
#X text 20 40 Listens for: /unity/colwall (bang from MockMidterm.pd's oscReceive);
#X text 20 65 Outputs: audio signal (mono) via [outlet~];
#X text 20 100 INTERNAL CONTROL BUS (set from MockMidterm.pd \, defaulted via loadbang on right):;
#X text 30 125 wall_lp_cutoff : low-pass cutoff in Hz (200-8000 \, default 1500 = thud weight);
#X text 20 160 TECHNIQUES (NES-authentic):;
#X text 30 185 - [noise~] -> [samphold~] driven by [phasor~] = pitched noise (NES samples random at the rate);
#X text 30 207 - Pitch envelope on samphold rate: 1500 Hz -> 200 Hz over 80 ms = boom-thud character;
#X text 30 229 - [lop~] for tone shaping (cutoff controllable via wall_lp_cutoff bus);
#X text 30 251 - Amp envelope: 1 5 \, 0 220 25 = sharp 5ms attack \, ~245ms tail (snappier than reference);
#X obj 60 290 r oscwall;
#X obj 60 330 t b b;
#X msg 60 370 1 5 \, 0 220 25;
#X obj 60 405 vline~;
#X msg 200 370 1500 0 \, 200 80 0;
#X obj 200 405 vline~;
#X obj 200 440 phasor~;
#X obj 350 400 noise~;
#X obj 280 475 samphold~;
#X obj 500 430 r wall_lp_cutoff;
#X obj 280 510 lop~;
#X obj 200 550 *~;
#X obj 200 590 outlet~;
#X obj 700 290 loadbang;
#X msg 700 325 1500;
#X obj 700 360 s wall_lp_cutoff;
#X text 700 395 (default LP cutoff set on patch load - slider in MockMidterm.pd then takes over);
